 from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Aeddan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Aidan</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aeddan ap Cydrych Arglwydd Grosmont was born about 1085, in Cardiganshire, Wales, his father, Gwaethfoed ap Clodien Mathew, was 11 and his mother, Morfydd Verch Ynyr, was 9. He married Anne verch Russell in 1125, in Glamorgan, Wales. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 2 daughters. He died in 1154, in Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"Abt 1085–1154":"umbes 1085–1154","1085–1154":"1085–1154","1104–1181":"1104–1181","1125–1161":"1125–1161","1127–Male":"1127–Surnud","1133–Male":"1133–Surnud","1175–1226":"1175–1226","1176–1259":"1176–1259","1075–1154":"1075–1154","1077–1104":"1077–1104","1154":"1154","1077":"1077","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1075":"1075","1085":"1085","1161":"1161","1181":"1181","Abt 1085":"umbes 1085","1127":"1127","1259":"1259","1226":"1226","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","about 1127":"umbes 1127",